    <!-- Application Structure Plan: The SPA is designed as a thematic educational journey, not a linear report. It uses a top navigation bar for direct access to key concepts: 1) Introduction sets the stage. 2) 'Core Distinction' offers an interactive side-by-side comparison, allowing users to actively explore differences. 3) 'Architectural Roles' clarifies their functions in thought. 4) 'The Journey of Meaning' interactively visualizes the complex Grady/Radden continuum model step-by-step, transforming a static theory into a dynamic process. 5) 'Modern Challenges' concludes with practical issues. This structure prioritizes user engagement and comprehension of abstract topics over simply reproducing the report's layout. -->
    <!-- Visualization & Content Choices: 1. Core Distinction (Table from report) -> Goal: Compare -> Viz: Interactive two-panel display with JS-powered buttons -> Interaction: User clicks criteria buttons ('Cognitive Basis', 'Syntactic Role') to dynamically update panel content, enabling direct, focused comparison. Justification: More engaging and less overwhelming than a static table. Method: HTML/CSS/JS. 2. Grady/Radden Continuum (Text description) -> Goal: Show Change/Process -> Viz: HTML/CSS flexbox-based process diagram combined with a Chart.js line chart -> Interaction: 'Next/Previous' buttons guide the user through stages (Conflation -> Deconflation). The chart lines visually diverge, representing the separation of concepts from metonymy to metaphor. Justification: Visualizes the abstract diachronic process, making it tangible and memorable. Method: HTML/CSS/JS + Chart.js (Canvas). 3. General Content -> Goal: Inform -> Viz: Styled text blocks with clear typography. Interaction: None. Justification: Ensures readability for foundational concepts. Method: HTML/Tailwind. -->
    <!-- CONFIRMATION: NO SVG graphics used. NO Mermaid JS used. -->
